# FreightFlow — Happy-Path Walkthrough
# VS Code REST Client — run each request with Ctrl+Alt+R
#
# Run in order, top to bottom. Each step depends on the previous one.
# Response values are extracted automatically via # @name annotations —
# no manual copy-pasting of IDs required.
#
# All requests go through the Gateway on port 8080.
# For direct-service testing during development, swap 8080 for 5000/5001.

@gateway = http://localhost:8080

# ─── Health checks (no auth required) ──────────────────────────────────────────

### Gateway health
GET {{gateway}}/health

### RFP API health (direct)
GET http://localhost:5000/health

### Carrier API health (direct)
GET http://localhost:5001/health

### Workflow Worker health (direct)
GET http://localhost:5002/health


# ─── Step 1 — Get a JWT ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Local dev stub. In production replace with Azure AD B2C / Keycloak.

# @name getToken
POST {{gateway}}/token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sub": "shipper-1",
  "role": "shipper"
}


# ─── Step 2 — Onboard a carrier ────────────────────────────────────────────────

# @name onboardCarrier
POST {{gateway}}/carriers
Authorization: Bearer {{getToken.response.body.$.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "dotNumber": "1234567",
  "name": "Acme Trucking LLC",
  "insuranceExpiry": "2027-12-31",
  "equipmentTypes": ["DryVan"],
  "certifications": [],
  "notes": null
}


# ─── Step 3 — Create an RFP ────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# @name createRfp
POST {{gateway}}/rfps
Authorization: Bearer {{getToken.response.body.$.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "shipperId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
  "maxBidRounds": 3,
  "openAt": "2026-05-01T00:00:00Z",
  "closeAt": "2026-06-30T00:00:00Z"
}


# ─── Step 4 — Add a lane ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# @name addLane
POST {{gateway}}/rfps/{{createRfp.response.body.$.id}}/lanes
Authorization: Bearer {{getToken.response.body.$.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "originZip": "90210",
  "destZip": "10001",
  "freightClass": "Class70",
  "volume": 100
}


# ─── Step 5 — Open the RFP ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Open RFP (transitions Draft → Open; bids can now be submitted)
POST {{gateway}}/rfps/{{createRfp.response.body.$.id}}/open
Authorization: Bearer {{getToken.response.body.$.token}}


# ─── Step 6 — Submit a bid ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Idempotency-Key ensures a retry of this exact request returns the same 201.

# @name submitBid
POST {{gateway}}/rfps/{{createRfp.response.body.$.id}}/bids
Authorization: Bearer {{getToken.response.body.$.token}}
Idempotency-Key: bid-key-001
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "carrierId": "{{onboardCarrier.response.body.$.id}}",
  "lanePrices": [
    {
      "laneId": "{{addLane.response.body.$.id}}",
      "amount": 1250.00,
      "currency": "USD"
    }
  ]
}


# ─── Step 6b — Idempotency check (same key → same 201) ─────────────────────────

### Re-submit with same Idempotency-Key — should return the cached 201
POST {{gateway}}/rfps/{{createRfp.response.body.$.id}}/bids
Authorization: Bearer {{getToken.response.body.$.token}}
Idempotency-Key: bid-key-001
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "carrierId": "{{onboardCarrier.response.body.$.id}}",
  "lanePrices": [
    {
      "laneId": "{{addLane.response.body.$.id}}",
      "amount": 1250.00,
      "currency": "USD"
    }
  ]
}


# ─── Step 7 — Award the carrier ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Returns 202 Accepted — the award workflow (Saga) continues asynchronously.
# Watch freight-workflow-worker logs for state transitions.

### Award carrier (triggers AwardWorkflow saga via Outbox → RabbitMQ)
POST {{gateway}}/rfps/{{createRfp.response.body.$.id}}/awards
Authorization: Bearer {{getToken.response.body.$.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bidId": "{{submitBid.response.body.$.id}}"
}


# ─── Step 8 — Confirm final state ──────────────────────────────────────────────

### Get RFP (status should be Awarded; award.contractId populated after saga completes)
GET {{gateway}}/rfps/{{createRfp.response.body.$.id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{getToken.response.body.$.token}}


# ─── Rate-limit smoke test ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Uncomment and run in a loop to verify 429 responses after 1000 req/min per sub.
# for i in {1..105}; do curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}\n" \
#   -H "Authorization: Bearer <token>" http://localhost:8080/rfps/<id>; done
